  "response": "One of the best things someone did for me on my birthday was a surprise gesture that felt truly thoughtful and personal. A friend once organized a small gathering of my closest friends and family, coordinating it all in secret. They created a slideshow of cherished memories, laughter, and milestones we'd shared over the years, and everyone shared heartfelt messages. It wasn\u2019t extravagant, but the effort and love behind it made it unforgettable. It reminded me of the meaningful connections in my life, and that\u2019s what made it so special. Birthdays are about feeling seen and appreciated, and that moment did just that.",
